<p><a name="P248_95237" href="#P248_95238">105</a>  Some commenters stated that "aware" was an unclear term that may be interpreted to mean something less than "knowing possession."  We disagree.  "Aware" is a commonly used and well-defined English word, meaning "having knowledge; conscious; cognizant."  We believe that "awareness" has a much clearer meaning than "knowing possession," which has not been defined by case law.</p>
