<p><a name="P257_98408" href="#P257_98409">110</a>  Rule 10b5-1(c)(1)(i)(B).  We have removed the proposed affirmative defense for purchases or sales that result from a written plan for trading securities that is designed to track or correspond to a market index, market segment, or group of securities.  We believe that the activity that was contemplated by that provision is permissible under the defense as adopted.  Therefore, a separate defense is no longer necessary.</p>
